@DavidEGrayson that is exactly what I would have expected from a modern API.
C conventions aside. 

Chronology aside,  I also think the list of argument type orders is very cumbersome and difficult to remember,  and probably all round unnecessary.

@DavidEGrayson

> I'm aiming for following "out = f(in)" as much as possible, and retain that argument order when earlier outs become ins

That is,  composability of arguments comes from the front,  which makes sense if you look at how you would do it if you were following the: `secp256k1_ec_privkey_import :: secret <- (context -> privateKey)` grammar.

@sipa though,  given this reasoning,  why is the context at the front?
